{"body": "It seems like half of the logic of computing the table name lives in `compute_table_name` and half of it lives in `reset_table_name`.\n\nAs far as I can tell, `compute_table_name` is only called from `reset_table_name`. How about consolidating all of the computing logic into `compute_table_name`? That might make it easier to see what the next refactoring should be.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6880648", "created_at": "2012-07-10T16:25:39Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7011#issuecomment-6880648", "updated_at": "2012-07-10T16:25:39Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7011, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/kytrinyx", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/51ee7bed9ecbc33aec92517f1fbb6cc2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F9ff5c784e0839c867d3159c55e0a2c04.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/received_events", "gravatar_id": "51ee7bed9ecbc33aec92517f1fbb6cc2", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "kytrinyx", "type": "User", "id": 276834, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kytrinyx/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523800d4bd3543c15100c04b"}, "id": 6880648, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7011"}
